description:
&lt;p&gt;Ward 15 at the Royal Glamorgan Hospital specialises in Rehabilitation. Primarily our patients are admitted following orthopaedic hip and femur surgery, and includes those patients with medical/surgical backgrounds who require enhanced Physiotherapy or Occupational Therapy prior to discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will give the successful candidate a wide range of opportunities for development and progression in these fields, to become a member of a successful multidisciplinary team, to participate in and then steer complex discharge planning. We pride ourselves on core nursing skills with strong emphasis on fundamental nursing principles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Justin Hughes&lt;br /&gt;Ward Manager&lt;br /&gt;01443 443443 ext 73515/73325&lt;br /&gt;justin.hughes@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
